    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fabric of wool or wool blend with one glossy side, originating in Flanders, ca. 18th century. Calamanco traditionally is woven with a checker in the warp so that it is seen on the glossy side only.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
